1. Color Palette (High-End & Trustworthy)
Design mein Neutral Tones ka bahut sahi use hua hai. Used items ke liye ye isliye accha hai kyunki photos colourful hongi, toh background clean chahiye.

Primary Background: #E2E5E6 (Wo light grey/off-white jo video mein hai. Ye white se better lagta hai.)

Deep Dark (Text/Buttons): #0F1110 (Ekdum jet black nahi, thoda soft dark.)

Accent Color (Interactions): #C5C7C5 (Hover states aur secondary buttons ke liye.)

Card Background: #FFFFFF (Items ke cards ko lift dene ke liye pure white use kar.)

2. Component List (For Your Platform)
Video ke layout ko dekh kar ye components tere "Used Items" app/web ke liye perfect rahenge:

Glassmorphic Navbar: Top par transparent ya blur background wala nav jisme "Rent", "Buy", "Sell" ke options ho.

Hero Slider: Jaise video mein model change ho raha hai, wahan tu high-quality "Featured Ads" ya "Nearby Deals" dikha sakta hai.

Category Grid: "Fresh Fits For Your Next Workout" wale section ki tarah tu "Electronics", "Furniture", "Vehicles" ke cards bana.

Bento-style Product Cards: Ek bada card, do chhote cards ka mix (jaisa video ke middle mein hai). Ye "Trending Items" dikhane ke liye mast lagega.

Floating Action Button (FAB): Ek bada round button "Sell Item" ke liye, jo screen par hamesha rahe.

Micro-Interactions: Jab user item par hover kare, toh image halki si zoom ho ya price pop-up ho (jaise video mein transitions ho rahe hain).